Name:          Albert Einstein
Lived:         1879 - 1955
Nationality:   German-American
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Theory of Relativity
Contribution:  E=mc2; photoelectric effect; special and general relativity
Quote:         "Imagination is more important than knowledge."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

Name:          Galileo Galilei
Lived:         1564 - 1642
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Astronomy
Known For:     Heliocentrism, telescope
Contribution:  Confirmed Copernican model; law of falling bodies; faced Inquisition
Quote:         "And yet it moves."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

